* {{audio|en|en-us-consumption.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|-|s}}

# The act of eating, drinking or using.
#: ''The '''consumption''' of snails as food is more common in France than in England.''
# The amount [[consume]]d.
#: ''gross national '''consumption'''''
# The act of [[consume|consuming]] or [[destroy]]ing.
#: ''The fire's '''consumption''' of the forest caused ecological changes.''
# {{lb|en|pathology}} The [[waste away|wasting away]] of the human body through [[disease]].
# {{senseid|en|TB}}{{lb|en|pathology|dated}} [[pulmonary tuberculosis|Pulmonary tuberculosis]] and other diseases that cause wasting away, lung infection, etc.

